From 2a24abc639763332c0ff32cbc03a78f669ae03a0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nathan Wilson <nath.flagman151@passmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 08:30:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] CUDA: dequantize KV on load in the tile FA kernel, use it
 for quantized decode

The vec kernel fuses dequantization into the KQ dot product, so a dequantized KV
value is never materialized and cannot be reused. It also assigns one Q head per
block (K += nb12*(head / gqa_ratio)), so each of the gqa_ratio Q heads sharing a
KV head re-dequantizes it in its own block. At decode there is nothing to
amortize this against (n=1), so quantized-KV decode does gqa_ratio times more
dequant work than necessary.

The tile kernel already batches ncols2 Q heads per block and stages KV in SRAM,
which is the structure the reuse needs -- it just could not consume quantized KV,
so launch_fattn was called with need_f16_K/V hardcoded to true, forcing a
full-cache pre-dequant into an f16 scratch buffer.

Add flash_attn_tile_load_tile_q, which dequantizes into the SRAM tile on load;
template type_K/type_V through the tile call chain (defaulted to F16, so f16
paths are unchanged); derive need_f16_K/V from those types; and prefer tile for
symmetric q4_0/q8_0 KV when the GQA optimization applies, mirroring the f16
branch. The KV tile is then dequantized once per block and reused by all ncols2
heads.

The loader is bound by per-thread-chunk overhead rather than by bytes, so the
chunk size (epc) is kept equal across KV types and narrower types issue several
dequantize_V calls per chunk: q8_0 decodes 8 elements in one call, q4_0 needs two
4-element calls because it decodes nibbles through a 4-byte int. Matching the
chunk size this way is worth ~10% for q4_0 at depth.

Measured on gfx1151 (Radeon 8060S), tg32 t/s, stock vs patched:

  Qwen3-Coder-30B-A3B (head_dim 128, gqa_ratio 8)
    depth   q8_0 stock -> patched    q4_0 stock -> patched    f16
    16k       26.59      43.20         26.29      45.69      41.20
    32k       16.65      38.14         17.55      39.97      31.97
    64k        8.86      28.96          9.35      31.65      22.17

  Llama-3.2-1B (head_dim 64, gqa_ratio 4)   q8_0 32k: 83.42 -> 102.06
  Qwopus3.6-35B-A3B (head_dim 256, gqa 8)   q8_0 32k: 37.55 ->  40.89

Quantized KV decode goes from behind f16 to ahead of it, matching the Vulkan
backend, which batches GQA and does not have this problem. Against a bandwidth
model fitted on the f16/tile arms, q8_0 decode at 32k moves from 41% of its
bandwidth ceiling to 95%; q4_0 reaches 85%, the remainder being its more
expensive nibble unpack.

f16 is unchanged. Prefill is unaffected at head_dim 64/128 (the mma path already
handles it); at head_dim 256 prefill already used tile and now dequantizes on
load instead of pre-dequantizing to f16.
